 {"id":"br-r37-c1-02","title":"REVIEW: [MEDIUM] node_connectivity on MultiGraph with parallel edges returned simple-graph value","description":"fnx.node_connectivity(MultiGraph) called into _raw_node_connectivity which collapses parallel edges. On e.g. K3 with extra parallel edges between two pairs, networkx returns min-degree=3 (parallel edges inflate the degree bound) while fnx returned 2 (simple-graph κ=n−1). Fixed by delegating multigraph inputs to networkx to preserve parity. Simple Graph/DiGraph continue to use the Rust fast path.","status":"closed","priority":3,"issue_type":"bug","created_at":"2026-04-24T00:00:00Z","updated_at":"2026-04-24T00:00:00Z","closed_at":"2026-04-24T00:00:00Z","close_reason":"Fixed: node_connectivity now delegates when G.is_multigraph(). Verified on K3-parallel, K3 MG no-parallel, MDG with parallel edges — all match nx.","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0}
 {"id":"br-r37-c1-03","title":"REVIEW: [MEDIUM] edge_connectivity returned float and ignored MultiGraph parallel edges","description":"Two related defects in edge_connectivity: (1) simple Graph path returned a float (e.g. 2.0) via the max-flow pipeline while nx returns an int cardinality (2). (2) MultiGraph path collapsed parallel edges: on K3 with extra parallel edges fnx returned 2.0 vs nx's 3. Fixed by coercing int-valued floats to int before returning, and delegating multigraph inputs to networkx.","status":"closed","priority":3,"issue_type":"bug","created_at":"2026-04-24T00:00:00Z","updated_at":"2026-04-24T00:00:00Z","closed_at":"2026-04-24T00:00:00Z","close_reason":"Fixed: MG/MDG delegate to nx; simple Graph path casts integral float back to int. Verified across K3 simple, DG, MG with/without parallel, MDG — all match nx in value and type.","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0}
 {"id":"br-r37-c1-19x8x","title":"parity: ISMAGS class missing from isomorphism API","description":"NetworkX exposes networkx.algorithms.isomorphism.ISMAGS(graph, subgraph, node_match=None, edge_match=None, cache=None) with is_isomorphic(), isomorphisms_iter(), subgraph_is_isomorphic(), subgraph_isomorphisms_iter(), and largest_common_subgraph(). FrankenNetworkX does not export ISMAGS. Add an ISMAGS wrapper that converts FrankenNetworkX graph objects via _networkx_graph_for_parity and delegates to NetworkX, plus parity tests for constructor signature and core methods.","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","assignee":"cod-networkx","created_at":"2026-04-25T09:25:45.112099160Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-04-25T09:30:32.434165705Z","closed_at":"2026-04-25T09:30:32.432309961Z","close_reason":"Completed in 2c0f4aa","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0}
+{"id":"br-r37-c1-7u6up","title":"parity: community edge_betweenness_partition + greedy_source_expansion missing","description":"Two community-detection helpers from networkx.algorithms.community not exposed by franken_networkx: edge_betweenness_partition(G, number_of_sets, weight=None) and greedy_source_expansion(G, source, ...). Add Python wrappers delegating via _call_networkx_community_for_parity, export at top-level and add to __all__.","status":"open","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-04-25T12:13:47.981273951Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-04-25T12:13:47.981273951Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0}
 {"id":"br-r37-c1-9mdsv","title":"parity: label_propagation_communities return type drift","description":"fnx.label_propagation_communities(G) returns dict_values([{0,1,2},...]) — a dict_values view object — while networkx returns a generator yielding sets. Drop-in code that does isinstance(result, types.GeneratorType) or relies on consuming once will diverge. Convert wrapper to yield sets directly (return iter(...)). File: python/franken_networkx/__init__.py (around line 17175).","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-04-25T05:05:05.214287589Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-04-25T05:08:52.048798239Z","closed_at":"2026-04-25T05:08:52.046958637Z","close_reason":"Invalid: NetworkX 3.6.1 and legacy oracle both return dict_values; existing wrapper and tests already match.","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0}
 {"id":"br-r37-c1-cujmq","title":"parity: VF2 GraphMatcher/DiGraphMatcher/MultiGraphMatcher classes missing","description":"networkx.algorithms.isomorphism exposes GraphMatcher, DiGraphMatcher, MultiGraphMatcher, MultiDiGraphMatcher classes for the classical VF2 algorithm with rich API: subgraph_is_isomorphic(), subgraph_isomorphisms_iter(), match(), candidate_pairs_iter(), semantic_feasibility(), syntactic_feasibility(), initialize(). fnx exposes only the top-level functions (is_isomorphic, vf2pp_*) but no Matcher classes. Add wrapper classes that delegate to nx.algorithms.isomorphism via _networkx_graph_for_parity, exporting as fnx.GraphMatcher etc.","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","assignee":"cod-networkx","created_at":"2026-04-25T07:30:43.669346473Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-04-25T09:18:29.924704555Z","closed_at":"2026-04-25T09:18:29.922845114Z","close_reason":"Completed in 742c813","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0}
 {"id":"br-r37-c1-f64cy","title":"parity: pagerank silently falls back to unweighted when weight attr is missing","description":"fnx.pagerank(G, weight='nope') on a graph whose edges lack a 'nope' attribute returns the unweighted result instead of raising. NetworkX defaults the missing attribute to 1 (treated as edge weight 1) — semantically same as unweighted but only when ALL edges lack the key. fnx behavior is similar but should be verified against nx for partial-attribute graphs (some edges weighted, others missing). Add parity test that builds a graph where half the edges have weight, half don't, and asserts fnx and nx agree to 1e-9.","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-04-25T08:26:41.408497679Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-04-25T09:11:17.258068772Z","closed_at":"2026-04-25T09:11:17.256114832Z","close_reason":"Verified parity. fnx.pagerank already matches nx exactly on per-edge default-1 fallback for missing weight attributes — no code fix needed. Landed tests/python/test_pagerank_weight_parity.py (commit 400eefe) with 6 cases pinning the contract: all-weighted, weight='nope' (all missing), partial weights (half missing), weight=None, DiGraph partial, plus a sanity check that asymmetric weights produce a non-trivial pagerank delta vs unweighted (proving the implementation isn't in a hidden global fallback path).","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0}
 {"id":"br-r37-c1-h41f2","title":"parity: isomorphism match helper functions missing","description":"NetworkX exposes categorical_node_match, categorical_edge_match, categorical_multiedge_match, numerical_node_match, numerical_edge_match, numerical_multiedge_match, generic_node_match, generic_edge_match, and generic_multiedge_match from networkx.algorithms.isomorphism. FrankenNetworkX does not export these helpers, so callback construction for GraphMatcher and is_isomorphic differs. Add wrappers delegating to networkx.algorithms.isomorphism and parity tests covering node/edge/multiedge helper behavior.","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","assignee":"cod-networkx","created_at":"2026-04-25T09:19:58.209906853Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-04-25T09:24:21.965842231Z","closed_at":"2026-04-25T09:24:21.963986187Z","close_reason":"Completed in bc5cd31","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0}
+{"id":"br-r37-c1-hq5pq","title":"parity: connectivity minimum_st_edge_cut missing","description":"networkx.algorithms.connectivity.minimum_st_edge_cut(G, s, t, flow_func=None, auxiliary=None, residual=None) returns minimum st edge cut. Not exposed by franken_networkx (only minimum_edge_cut and minimum_st_node_cut exist). Add Python wrapper delegating to networkx and export at top-level.","status":"open","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-04-25T11:59:43.139262003Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-04-25T11:59:43.139262003Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0}
 {"id":"br-r37-c1-lmviu","title":"parity: add_path/add_cycle/add_star keyword parameter names","description":"NetworkX exposes add_path(G_to_add_to, nodes_for_path, **attr), add_cycle(G_to_add_to, nodes_for_cycle, **attr), and add_star(G_to_add_to, nodes_for_star, **attr). FNX currently names these parameters G and nodes, so documented keyword calls like fnx.add_path(G_to_add_to=G, nodes_for_path=[1,2]) raise TypeError. Align the public signatures while preserving positional behavior and add parity tests.","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","assignee":"cod-networkx","created_at":"2026-04-25T06:20:06.172080189Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-04-25T06:23:19.168859030Z","closed_at":"2026-04-25T06:23:19.167009410Z","close_reason":"Completed in 92bae80","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0}
+{"id":"br-r37-c1-lz7u6","title":"parity: connectivity bridge_components missing","description":"networkx.algorithms.connectivity.bridge_components(G) returns 2-edge-connected components after removing bridges. Not exposed by franken_networkx. Add Python wrapper delegating to nx.algorithms.connectivity.bridge_components via _networkx_graph_for_parity, export at top-level and add to __all__.","status":"open","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-04-25T11:44:53.163889437Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-04-25T11:44:53.163889437Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0}
 {"id":"br-r37-c1-oiic9","title":"parity: all_pairs_node_connectivity flow_func ignored + iteration order","description":"fnx.all_pairs_node_connectivity(G, nbunch=None, flow_func=None) accepts flow_func but ignores it (always uses default max-flow). Also outer/inner dict iteration order differs from networkx for K4: fnx outer order is 1,0,2,3 while nx is 0,1,2,3. Honor flow_func by delegating to nx when provided, and stabilize iteration order (use G.nodes() insertion order). Located in python/franken_networkx/__init__.py near the existing all_pairs_node_connectivity wrapper.","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","assignee":"cod-networkx","created_at":"2026-04-25T04:58:20.898200931Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-04-25T05:05:56.920452351Z","closed_at":"2026-04-25T05:05:56.918586339Z","close_reason":"Completed in f14208d","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0}
 {"id":"br-r37-c1-qyx9u","title":"parity: top-level isomorphism module missing","description":"NetworkX exposes nx.isomorphism as a top-level module containing GraphMatcher, DiGraphMatcher, ISMAGS, time-respecting matchers, match helper constructors, is_isomorphic, vf2pp_* helpers, and tree isomorphism helpers. FrankenNetworkX currently exports these names only at top level and lacks fnx.isomorphism / import franken_networkx.isomorphism. Add a module object backed by the FrankenNetworkX wrappers and register it in sys.modules, plus parity tests proving the module points at the wrapper classes/functions.","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","assignee":"cod-networkx","created_at":"2026-04-25T09:37:49.312623478Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-04-25T09:42:21.985411035Z","closed_at":"2026-04-25T09:42:21.983510716Z","close_reason":"Completed in 56128df","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0}
 {"id":"br-r37-c1-sgjko","title":"parity: time-respecting isomorphism matchers missing","description":"NetworkX exposes TimeRespectingGraphMatcher(G1, G2, temporal_attribute_name, delta) and TimeRespectingDiGraphMatcher(G1, G2, temporal_attribute_name, delta). FrankenNetworkX does not export these classes, leaving temporal VF2 matcher API unavailable. Add wrappers that convert FrankenNetworkX graph objects via _networkx_graph_for_parity and delegate to NetworkX, plus parity tests for signatures and isomorphism mappings on temporal graph/digraph paths.","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","assignee":"cod-networkx","created_at":"2026-04-25T09:31:58.717555427Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-04-25T09:35:34.565138940Z","closed_at":"2026-04-25T09:35:34.563236879Z","close_reason":"Completed in 739ccaa","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0}
+{"id":"br-r37-c1-vw7p2","title":"parity: connectivity is_locally_k_edge_connected missing","description":"networkx.algorithms.connectivity.is_locally_k_edge_connected(G, s, t, k) tests local k-edge-connectivity between s and t. Not exposed by franken_networkx. Add Python wrapper delegating to networkx and export at top-level.","status":"open","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-04-25T11:51:45.929293966Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-04-25T11:51:45.929293966Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0}
+{"id":"br-r37-c1-wpydo","title":"parity: community leiden_communities + leiden_partitions missing","description":"networkx.algorithms.community.leiden_communities(G, ...) and leiden_partitions(G, ...) (Leiden community detection algorithm) not exposed by franken_networkx. Add Python wrappers delegating to nx.algorithms.community via _call_networkx_community_for_parity. Export both at top-level and include in __all__ under community detection section.","status":"open","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-04-25T12:06:41.073069778Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-04-25T12:06:41.073069778Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0}
 {"id":"br-r37-c1-xditv","title":"parity: fruchterman_reingold_layout numeric parity with networkx","description":"fnx.fruchterman_reingold_layout / spring_layout share signatures with nx but numeric outputs are not pinned to nx for the same seed and graph. Add a parity test (tests/python/test_layout_parity.py) that builds a small fixed graph (path_graph(6), complete_graph(5), karate_club_graph), seeds with seed=42, and compares fnx vs nx node positions within tolerance 1e-6. If divergence, route to nx via _call_networkx_for_parity when method='auto' to preserve drop-in behavior.","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","assignee":"cod-networkx","created_at":"2026-04-25T06:14:51.495203398Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-04-25T06:18:38.622702670Z","closed_at":"2026-04-25T06:18:38.620786474Z","close_reason":"Completed in 82fb1eb","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0}
 {"id":"br-r38-c1-01","title":"REVIEW: [HIGH] signature mismatches blocked nx drop-in kwarg calls (8 functions)","description":"A signature sweep comparing every fnx public function against its networkx counterpart surfaced real drop-in breakage. Missing nx-style kwargs caused TypeErrors on documented calls:\n\n- fiedler_vector: missing tol, method, seed\n- spectral_ordering: missing weight, tol, method, seed\n- spectral_bisection: missing normalized, tol, method, seed\n- incidence_matrix: missing keyword-only dtype\n- attr_matrix: missing order (numpy memory layout) AND wrong return shape — fnx always returned a (matrix, labels) tuple, but nx returns just the matrix when rc_order is supplied\n- attr_sparse_matrix: same return-shape defect as attr_matrix\n- has_path: first positional named 'graph'; nx names it 'G' (broke has_path(G=x,...))\n- harmonic_diameter / hyper_wiener_index: missing weight\n- duplication_divergence_graph: missing create_using\n- bfs_labeled_edges: parameter named 'source' (single) instead of nx's 'sources' (iterable)\n- dfs_labeled_edges: missing keyword-only sort_neighbors\n- is_connected_dominating_set: second param named 'S' instead of nx's 'nbunch'\n\nAll fixed to accept the same kwargs as networkx; where semantically meaningful (weight on wiener/harmonic, dtype on incidence_matrix, order on attr_matrix) the kwarg now affects the result. Others (tol/method/seed on the dense spectral solvers) are accepted for signature parity and noted as ignored by the deterministic numpy.linalg.eigh path.","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"bug","created_at":"2026-04-24T00:00:00Z","updated_at":"2026-04-24T00:00:00Z","closed_at":"2026-04-24T00:00:00Z","close_reason":"Fixed signatures + return shapes. Verified each fixed function with nx-style kwargs; existing parity tests still pass.","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0}
 {"id":"br-r38-c1-02","title":"REVIEW: [HIGH] to_prufer_sequence panicked (Rust) on non-tree / bad labels instead of raising NotATree","description":"fnx.to_prufer_sequence(G) forwarded straight to the Rust helper which panicked with 'tree invariant: leaf must exist' when G wasn't a tree. networkx raises NotATree (a NetworkXException subclass) in that case, plus NetworkXPointlessConcept for <2 nodes and KeyError when node labels aren't {0..n-1}. PanicException bypasses ordinary except blocks in user code. Fixed by validating is_directed / node count / is_tree / node labels in Python before calling into Rust, matching nx's exception contract exactly.","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"bug","created_at":"2026-04-24T00:00:00Z","updated_at":"2026-04-24T00:00:00Z","closed_at":"2026-04-24T00:00:00Z","close_reason":"Fixed: validate in Python, raise NetworkXPointlessConcept / NotATree / KeyError as appropriate; verified on karate_club_graph, empty graph, and string-labelled trees — all raise the same exception types as nx.","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0}
